benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to payment

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC17, TC18, TC20 cover standard successful update flows with 204 responses and data consistency.
Non-Existing Resource: TC06 covers 404 when payment not found.

Partial Update / Validation: TC05 (invalid paymentId), TC07 (missing header), TC08 (missing body), TC09 (malformed JSON), TC10 (invalid content), TC13 (injection/security validation), TC16 (unexpected extra properties) provide validation and error handling coverage.
Authorization: TC11 tests unauthorized access returns 401.
Server Error Handling: TC12 tests 500 on system/database failure.
Security: TC13 covers input security/invalid content scenarios.
Large Payloads / Edge Cases: TC14 and TC20 cover large payloads and performance-focused edge cases.
Duplication Handling: TC18 tests behavior with duplicate field names.
Integration/Data Consistency: TC17 confirms GET reflects update after PUT.
Performance / Concurrency: TC19 validates concurrent requests and general performance expectations.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets in GET/PUT contexts.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify caching headers or ETag behavior for PUT responses.
Rate Limiting: No tests validate throttling or rate limiting across multiple PUT requests.
Partial Update nuance: While there is broad validation, explicit separate test for partial update semantics (only subset of fields updated) is not clearly distinct from full update flows.
Empty Response semantics: Although 204 is used on success, explicit tests for empty or no-op responses in edge cases are not isolated.
recommendations: Add pagination-focused tests for GET/PUT when dealing with large numbers of custom fields.
Add caching validation tests (ETag/Cache-Control) for PUT responses.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under load.
Add an explicit Partial Update scenario if API supports partial field updates distinct from full replacement, to validate allowed/disallowed changes.
